&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Full time, permanent Specialty Doctor position at Dorset County Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join the pathology team at Dorset County Hospital. We are currently making great progress with our vision to create a first class integrated pathology service for Dorset. The ‘One Dorset Pathology’ service for Dorset County Hospital, Poole Hospital and The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals will provide clinicians, patients and carers with a consistent and high standard of service across the area and maximise efficiency in the use of resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Dorset County Hospital, the Diagnostic work includes surgical pathology, non-gynaecology cytopathology and covers all major disciplines except gynaecology cytopathology, cardiac pathology and neuropathology. There is an opportunity to be involved in providing renal pathology for the regional Renal Unit based in Dorchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameProfessor Mohamed SattiJob titleConsultant Histopathologist &amp; Clinical LeadEmail addressmohamed.satti@dchft.nhs.ukTelephone number01305 254831Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or informal visits, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neil Johnston, Care Group Service manager on 01305 253761 or Neil.johnston@dchft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
